The five-membered ring provides a rigid structure that can increase the melting point due to a higher degree of crystallinity compared to an open-chain compound. This effect is estimated to add +20 to the melting point. When summing these effects, the expected adjustment would be (+40) + (-30) + (+20) = +30 from the baseline of succinimide. Since the methyl group would have a relatively small effect compared to the others, we can ignore its contribution for this estimation.
